messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full request path:
- /api/profiles/{username}/follow

All methods acceptable:
- false

Methods accepted by the code (based on routing registration):
- HEAD: false
- POST: true  (registered in ProfileRegister as router.POST("/:username/follow", ProfileFollow))
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true (registered in ProfileRegister as router.DELETE("/:username/follow", ProfileUnfollow))
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In main (hello.go) the routes are mounted under the "/api" group: v1 := r.Group("/api").
- Profile routes are registered with users.ProfileRegister(v1.Group("/profiles")), so the profiles group prefix is "/profiles" under "/api".
- In users/routers.go ProfileRegister sets router.POST("/:username/follow", ProfileFollow) and router.DELETE("/:username/follow", ProfileUnfollow). Combining prefixes yields the full path /api/profiles/{username}/follow.
- The code explicitly registers POST and DELETE handlers for that path. No handlers for HEAD, GET, PUT, PATCH, OPTIONS or TRACE are registered for that exact path in the provided code, so those methods are not acceptable according to the code.
